	 		 <div class="vertical-post-flex-item-left"><div class="vertical-post-intro"><h1>Treatments for Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder (OCD)</h1><p class="dates"><strong>Published on:</strong> March 3, 2025</p><p><em>In this episode, Dr. Chu discusses obsessive-compulsive disorder in children, including its signs, symptoms, and how it differs from anxiety.</em></p><p class="print"><strong>Link: </strong>https://health.choc.org/podcasts/treatments-for-obsessive-compulsive-disorder/</p></div></div>
			 <div class="vertical-post-flex-item-right" style="background-image:url(https://health.choc.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/OCD-in-kids-1.jpg)"></div>
			 </div><div class="site-inner"><div class="content-sidebar-wrap">
<div style="background-color:#efefef" class="wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-container content-box gb-block-container"><div class="gb-container-inside"><div class="gb-container-content">
<p class="has-text-align-center has-theme-secondary-color has-text-color wp-block-paragraph" style="font-size:30px"><strong>Crisis Resources</strong></p>



<p class="has-text-align-center wp-block-paragraph">If your child expresses thoughts of wanting to harm themselves or others,<br>call&nbsp;<strong>9-1-1</strong>&nbsp;or visit the nearest emergency department.<br>To reach the Crisis Text Line, text HOME to 741-741 or visit&nbsp;<a href="http://www.crisistextline.org/">crisistextline.org</a>.<br>To reach the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline, call 9-8-8 or visit&nbsp;<a href="https://988lifeline.org/" type="link" id="https://988lifeline.org/">988lifeline.org</a>.</p>
</div></div></div>
<main class="content" id="genesis-content"><article class="post-31002 podcasts type-podcasts status-publish has-post-thumbnail category-mental-health tag-michael-chu-md entry" aria-label="Treatments for Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder (OCD)"><div class="entry-content">
<figure class="wp-block-audio"><audio controls="" src="https://health.choc.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/choc007.mp3"></audio></figure>



